<p>Dear Sudheer,</p>
<p>Working with you was a great pleasure. &nbsp;Your sense of purpose, dedi=
cation, imagination,&nbsp;balanced&nbsp;viewpoints, and fine inter-personal=
 relationships with so many persons within and outside our Institute&nbsp;a=
re worthy of&nbsp;wider recognition.</p>
<p><br>
</p>
<p>Your persistent efforts to have the unparalleled sports facilities in ou=
r campus (the two new Squash courts, our Swimming Pool, the Manohar C. Wats=
a stadium, the Roller Skating rink, the Basketball court at OAT, etc.) comm=
issioned and maintained properly,
 or repaired and recovered effectively, deserve full praise.</p>
<p><br>
</p>
<p>I'm sure you would have been a perfect host during the inter-IIT meet pl=
anned to be organized in December 2015. &nbsp;The cyclone and floods then r=
obbed us of the opportunity to showcase our sports and games facilities to =
the various inter-IIT contingents that
 would have otherwise enjoyed our campus.&nbsp; <br>
</p>
<p><br>
</p>
<p>I must confess that i have often wondered how you maintained a near perf=
ect balance between your academic work, efforts, and accomplishments on the=
 one hand with the contributions you made as Advisor (Sports) to life in ou=
r Institute on the other,&nbsp;while&nbsp;contributing
 to a very cheerful family.&nbsp; Great work, Sudheer! <br>
</p>
<p><br>
</p>
<p>Please accept my&nbsp;best wishes to you and all in your family for very=
 cheerful and healthy&nbsp;times ahead.</p>
<p><br>
</p>
<p>Of course, my best wishes are also meant for Professor Santosh, your suc=
cessor, who will certainly&nbsp;set&nbsp;new standards and benchmarks durin=
g his tenure as Advisor (Sports).<br>
</p>
<p><br>
